DIGEST
SB 25 Re-Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Kleinpeter
Present law provides pay schedules for registrars of voters, their chief deputies, and
confidential assistants. Compensation is determined based on the population of the parish
and the years of experience of the individual. Years of experience are provided as steps on
the salary schedule.
Proposed law adjusts the present law steps to reduce the number of population levels and the
number of steps and to increase the compensation in the steps of the schedule for registrars
of voters, chief deputies, and confidential assistants.
Proposed law requires that any registrar, chief deputy, or confidential assistant whose salary
has remained at the level of step ten for more than 12 months receive a 5% salary increase
upon a finding of "excellent"on the merit evaluation. No registrar, chief deputy, or
confidential assistant shall receive more than five such annual salary increases.
Present law provides the methods by which the population of each parish is determined
including data from estimates by La. Tech.
Proposed law adjusts the methods by which the population of each parish is determined but
removes data estimates by La. Tech.
Proposed law adds population figures from the latest federal decennial census published
pursuant to the United States Bureau of the Census Federal State Cooperative Program for
Population Estimates.
Proposed law adds provision that Dept. of State shall not adjust the annual salary of
registrars of voters except once decennially one year after receiving the federal census.
Proposed law adds provision that Dept. of State shall not adjust the annual salary of chief
deputy registrars of voters and confidential assistant to the registrars of voters- except once
decennially one year after receiving the federal census.
Effective July 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 18:55(A)(1), (2), and (4)(b), and (C), 59(B)(1), (2), and (4)(b), and (C)(1), (2),
and (4)(b), and (E); adds R.S. 18:55(G) and 59(N))
