Summary of Amendments Adopted by Senate
Committee Amendments Proposed by Senate Committee on Senate and
Governmental Affairs to the original bill
1. Provides for new source of information for population estimates as shown by
the latest federal decennial census published pursuant to the United States
Bureau of the Census Federal State Cooperative Program for Population
Estimates.
2. Limits salary adjustments for registrars of voters to once decennially one
year after receiving the federal census.
3. Provides for new source of information for population estimates as shown by
the latest federal decennial census published pursuant to the United States
Bureau of the Census Federal State Cooperative Program for Population
Estimates.
4. Limits salary adjustments for chief deputy registrars of voters and
confidential assistant to the registrars of voters to once decennially one year
after receiving the federal census.
Committee Amendments Proposed by Senate Committee on Finance to the
engrossed bill
1. Adjusts the compensation and reduce the number of steps in the schedules for
registrars of voters, chief deputies, and confidential assistants.
2. Provides for an annual 5% salary increase for registrars of voters, chief
deputies, and confidential assistants in certain circumstances.
3. Makes technical changes.
